<h1> code
 </h1>
<p>
&#39;&#39;code&#39;&#39; is cool. You can also use markdown-style &#39;`&#39;, which is more code-friendly and shorter but a bit harder to type.
&#39;&#39;&#39;
plain multiline code snippets also work
&#39;&#39;&#39;
```
3 backticks do the same thing
```

</p>
<h2> tables
 </h2>
<p>
tables are of the form `#&lt;delimiter&gt;{}`. Delimiters can be multi-character.
The first row becomes the table header. Each item is trimmed of its whitespace

</p>
<table style="width:100%">
<tr>
<th>  </th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>  </td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
</p>
<h2> custom blocks
 </h2>
<p>
custom blocks are of the form `function:{input}`
Different translators will have different built-in functions. To run shell commands, prefix the function with `!`. Some translators have a secure mode that forbids these.

</p>
<h2> metadata
 </h2>
<p>
you can specify metadata in a &#39;&#39;@{}&#39;&#39; block, as key-value pairs of strings. These can be used by static site generators, Wikis and other programs
They need to be of the form `key = value`. Whitespace is trimmed
Additionaly, the shortcut &#39;&#39;=#&#39;&#39; exists which creates a `h1` element with its argument ==and== sets the &#39;&#39;title&#39;&#39; attribute to the content

</p>
